As the sun sets, PB transforms into a lively social hub with beach bars, rooftop lounges, and live music venues along Garnet Avenue.

name: La Jolla Retreat-ZenLife; 3 blocks to Ocean
description:
Cozy, quiet twin bed, shared bathroom, located on a magical, tree-lined street reminiscent of a country lane, nestled in a plethora of Mother Nature.

Off the beaten path, tranquility.

The ocean's breeze wafts through my home.

Ficus, decades-old majestic Yuccas, gardens, outdoor seating-eating options.

Serenity, walkability, biking, restaurants, coffee shops, outdoor yoga.

Look through the beaches of the SD book, those within 5 miles.
neighborhood_overview:
Tranquility, stately 'umbrella trees', meditative and zen-ful, my home is tucked away on a country lane ambiance yet blocks to:

Amazing sunsets, studios, shops, electric bike rentals, Pilates, decadently delicious Wayfarer Bakery, Lupi's Italian, Bahia don Bravo Mexican, Beaumont's, (our neighborhood version of Cheers) Wheat and Water pizza, salads, burgers etc, SurfSide Cafe for healthy snacks, sandwiches, wraps, smoothies, soups, Bird Rock Coffee Roasters=direct trade farm to coffee cup; outdoor yoga to live music at Riff's Studio.

Friendly community, ease of transportation via Uber/Lyft or download MTS Pronto app for bus service throughout San Diego.
host_about:
As a  La Jolla native, I have seen many changes to our sweet village by the sea.  The constant however is the horizon; it is this endless view of magic that is just three blocks from my home and a perfect place to enjoy morning coffee and evening wine.

I am the grandmother of five lovely grandchildren, a retired teacher having taught K through adult education, and a retired concierge from two magnificent local hotels.

Are there places you have traveled where you sense that you belong.....those places beyond the borders of your birth community?   It is one of my goals that your time in my home and our village by the sea gives you that sense of belonging.

Passionate about  hospitality, and meeting guests the world over, I look forward to  sharing the tranquility my coastal home and garden paradise provides.

description:

neighborhood_overview: Located on a quiet and eclectic street in a canyon with lots of trees and great neighbors.  There are grocery stores, restaurants, coffee shops, movie theatres, book stores and entertainment within a 10-15 walk. There are many beaches to visit within a 10-15 minute drive. Balboa Park and the San Diego Zoo are just a 5 minute drive, as is Little Italy, San Diego Bay and the Gaslamp, with much more to do along the waterfront. San Diego ROCKS!
host_about:
Stella and her husband, Richard have been Airbnb Super Hosts since 2011. Stella‚Äôs background is in hospitality, as an Executive Assistant, Outlet Manager, Guest Services Specialist, Operations Director and Concierge. Stella earned her experience in hospitality with many great upscale hotels to include Starwood, Sheraton, Intercontinental, La Valencia and The US Grant. She spent another 12 years in radio and television broadcasting for CBS TV8 and KFMB AM & FM, the historic 91X, Mighty 690, KBest, Y-95, Radio Latina and Z-90. 

Richard is an award winning Musician, Producer and Sound Engineer. He has owned and operated Blitz Recording Studios in San Diego for over 30 years, recording all genres of music and sound, books on tape, and more. He has played with many Rock N‚Äô Roll, Blues, and Jazz greats in the business. Honored recently for a Lifetime Achievement Award from the San Diego Music Awards, he is regarded as one of the most prominent recording engineers in the business. As a founding member of the Blitz Bros, Sons of Edison and contributing member of GTF Jazz, he is well-known in the Southern California area, and continues to play live and in the studio.

After a two year break during the pandemic, Stella and Richard look forward to welcoming you back to their clean, comfortable, safe and well located home.

name: LJ Village Home with private pool & spa
description: Located in the village of La Jolla - under a 5 minute walk to the shops & restaurants, and less than a mile from the beach.
neighborhood_overview:
La Jolla Village is full of shops and amazing restaurants.
The beaches range from wide and sandy, to rocky areas with little private coves.

The house is located in a quiet residential neighborhood 3 blocks from the edge of the "Village" and 10 blocks from the beaches - just far enough away that parking is not an issue even during the summer.
It is just below the La Jolla Country Club, and nearby is the beautiful Cove Park and famous Windansea Beach and about 5 mins to La Jolla Shores Beach and the Scripps Aquarium, 10 mins to Torrey Pines State Park and the world class Golf Course.
Within under 30 min you can be in downtown San Diego, and another not much further is the border to Mexico.
The San Diego Zoo, Balboa Park, Sea World, Legoland, and the Wild Animal Park are all within about 30 mins as well.
The Del Mar Racetrack is also not far, usually about 15 mis (but during racing season traffic can be extreme)
host_about:

We absolutely love La Jolla and our home there as well, so are very fortunate that sharing our home via Airbnb rentals has enabled us to keep it. 
We have family only a few houses away that has lived in LJ for over 50 years and helps with the day to day running of things when we are not there.

neighborhood_overview:
The cottage is located in the beautiful neghborhood of South Park. The streets here are laid out alphabetically by tree names. The cottage is located between Ash and Beech. The majority of restaurants are located on Beech, Grape, and Juniper. The grocery stores are located on Cedar (Food Bowl) and Grape (Target). The laundry mat is on Cedar (Posh Wash).Here you can do your own laundry or for $1.50/pound they will wash, dry, fold and seal in plastic and have it ready for you by the end of the day!

Two blocks from the cottage are a couple of shops, Harlands Brewing Company (beer and food), Kindred (Vegan) and Buona Forchetta restaurants, a yoga studio and a bootcamp gym. About a mile walk is the heart of South Park with boutique shops, a great burger place (The Station), and numerous other restaurants and bars. The Big Kitchen is a breakfast and lunch place where Whoopie Goldberg got her start as a dishwasher. The neighborhood also has an Indian restaurant (Curryosity), and

name: Spanish Revival Home with a View
description: This is true country living in the city!  My home is secluded in a quiet canyon on a private road with only 3 other houses.  Yet, with just a 3 minute walk up the road you can experience the vibrancy of International Restaurant Row.
neighborhood_overview: The best part of our neighborhood is how peaceful it is, while being only a few moments from a vibrant restaurant scene and the entrance to the freeway.
host_about:
I am a retired elementary teacher.  During my 37 years of teaching I was able to teach overseas for a year on three occasions...once in Ibiza, Spain and twice with the Fulbright Teacher Exchange program in England. I have traveled extensively all of my life and don't intend to stop anytime soon.  I avoid tours, opting for the unexpected, collecting many lifelong friends along the way.  I recently returned from a month in China and Tibet where my friend an I plotted our own visit.  Tibet was unforgettable...even with altitude sickness.

Of the many hats I have worn over the years, I am most proud of the one called "mom".  Currently, my daughter is a teacher in New York City after grad school at NYU. And, my devoted step-daughter is a professor at several local colleges...both following me into rewarding the field of education.

I have a small import business selling items mostly from Thailand.  This started when I returned with some bamboo purses that I could not carry without a compliment.  I soon added a succulent art component when buyers asked to purchase the plants I brought along to adorn my sales displays.  So, now I enjoy creating and selling succulent art using cuttings from my garden and my neighboring canyon.  The most popular items are currently those planted in shoes I find at second hand stores.  I have just been asked to create some pieces for a wedding for a second time.  This time I will be using martini glasses filled with jewels and succulents.  I love the creative experience as much as the added income!

I know what it is like to rent and share share one's accommodations.  I often travel by making house exchanges using the Intervac agency.  I rent my upstairs home when I'm away and the downstairs vacation rental apartment most of the time.  
I have been told that I am an easy guest.  I am low maintenance and usually find that humor is a good companion and tool.  The only food that I absolutely dislike is licorice!  I like to think of myself as a lifelong learner and so have my mind open to a wide range of books, music, movies and life experiences.  I have recently added sailing to my life experiences.  My dear partner, Tom, and I sailed his boat from San Diego to Seattle and now enjoy many opportunities to sail the San Juan islands on The Black Swan. We recently added a 43 foot ketch sailboat to our fun while in San Diego and offer sunset sails through Airbnb experiences. 

Life motto?  My teaching partner would probably remind me that I always said, "It will all work out."  And, it usually does.

neighborhood_overview:
Our condo is centrally located in the Mission Valley district of San Diego.

Mission Valley is easily accessible to all San Diego has to offer. Every major freeway leading into San Diego County passes by or through the valley. Thus, many attractions and suburbs are less than 20 minutes away.

Accessibility to Mission Valley is easy with the Metropolitan Transit System (MTS) Green Line . This trolley line travels in an east‚Äìwest direction through the heart of Mission Valley.
